    "summary": "Non-perturbative QCD in PANDA experiment at FAIR:\nCharmonium spectroscopy and search for exotic charm-mesons. Development of Electromagnetic Calorimeter. Development of trigger-less dead-time free readout system.\n\nPET detector developments for Medical Imaging:\ncrystal readout with pixel sensors: optimized time resolution, position resolution, depth-of-interaction determination.\n\nCosmic Neutrino Detection:\nNeutrino Detection with deep-sea neutrino telescope ANTARES; flux limits for cosmic neutrino sources; \ndevelopment of novel multi-PMT Optical Module for KM3NeT infrastructure.\n\nPhoton probes of hadronic matter:\nTAPS Collaboration at various laboratories, photon and neutral meson studies; nuclear Bremsstrahlung, thermalizing nuclear matter, azimuthal asymmetry of neutral mesons, photonuclear reactions.\n\nUltrarelativistic Heavy Ion Reactions:\nElectromagnetic Calorimetry for photons and neutral mesons in ultrarelativistivc heavy-ion reactions (WA80, WA93, WA98). Direct photons. Charged particle multiplicities. Circumstantial evidence for quark-gluon plasma.\n\nRelativistic Heavy Ion Reactions: Establishing collective flow of nuclear matter with Plastic Ball at LBL Berkeley.",
